      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The rise of social media has fundamentally shifted news consumption, moving it from traditional gatekeepers to personalized, algorithm-driven feeds. This environment allows misinformation to spread rapidly and bypass journalistic scrutiny, making it very easy for biased or fabricated content to look legitimate. Consequently, people are increasingly polarized, trusting sources that confirm their existing beliefs rather than relying on objective reporting. This has eroded trust in established media institutions across the board.",
